## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) (comes with Node.js)

### Usage

1. Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/safe-site/bothub.git
    ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

    ```bash
    cd telegram-bot-interface
    ```

3. Open `index.html` in your web browser.

## How to Use

1. **Choose a Bot:**
   - Select a bot from the dropdown menu.

2. **Enter Chat IDs:**
   - Enter the Telegram Chat IDs of the users you want to send messages to. Separate multiple Chat IDs with commas.

3. **Enter SMS Content:**
   - Type your message in the SMS Content textarea.

4. **Select Image (Optional):**
   - Optionally, you can select an image to send along with the message.

5. **Send Message:**
   - Click the "Send Message" button to send your message.

## Example Bots

These are some example bots that you can use in this tool:

- [AlertPulseBot](https://telegram.me/AlertPulseBot)
- [AlertRushBot](https://telegram.me/AlertRushBot)
- [HyperAlertsBot](https://telegram.me/HyperAlertsBot)
- [QuickNotifyRobot](https://telegram.me/QuickNotifyRobot)
- [NotifyNinjaRobot](https://telegram.me/NotifyNinjaRobot)

## Important Note

Ensure that you have started the bot on Telegram before attempting to send messages. If the user has not started the bot, messages cannot be sent to them.

